# WCAG 2.2 AA Compliance Rules

> **Target**: WCAG 2.2 Level AA conformance
> **Standard**: https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/
> **Severity levels**: MUST (violates AA if ignored), SHOULD (strongly recommended), PREFER (advisory)

---

## 1. Perceivable

### 1.1 Text Alternatives (SC 1.1.1)

- MUST: Every `<img>` has a meaningful `alt` attribute. Decorative images use `alt=""` with `aria-hidden="true"`.
- MUST: All icon-only buttons and links have `aria-label` or visually hidden text.
- MUST: Lucide icons used decoratively carry `aria-hidden="true"`. Icons conveying meaning carry an accessible name.
- MUST: Chart components (Recharts) include a screen-reader-only data table fallback using `sr-only` class.

### 1.2 Time-based Media (SC 1.2.x)

- SHOULD: If video or audio content is added, provide captions (prerecorded) and audio descriptions.

### 1.3 Adaptable

- MUST (SC 1.3.1 ‚Äî Info and Relationships): Use semantic HTML elements (`<header>`, `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`, `<table>`, `<form>`, `<label>`, `<fieldset>`, `<legend>`). Never use `<div>` or `<span>` where a semantic element exists.
- MUST: Every form control has an associated `<label htmlFor>` or `aria-label`. Placeholder text alone is NOT a label.
- MUST: All `<Switch>` components have a paired `<label>` element with `htmlFor` matching the switch `id`. Never use a bare `<span>` as a label.
- MUST: Table elements maintain native table semantics. Never apply `display: flex` or `display: grid` to `<tr>`, `<th>`, or `<td>` elements ‚Äî this breaks assistive technology table navigation.
- MUST: Heading hierarchy is sequential (`h1` ‚Üí `h2` ‚Üí `h3`). Never skip levels. Sidebar group labels use `<p>` or proper heading level, not `<h4>` out of context.
- MUST (SC 1.3.4 ‚Äî Orientation): Do not lock content to a single display orientation unless essential.
- MUST (SC 1.3.5 ‚Äî Identify Input Purpose): Use `autocomplete` attributes on input fields collecting personal data (name, email, address, phone, etc.).

### 1.4 Distinguishable

- MUST (SC 1.4.1 ‚Äî Use of Color): Never rely on color alone to convey information. Status badges, compliance indicators, and chart data MUST use a secondary differentiator: icon, text label, or pattern.
- MUST (SC 1.4.3 ‚Äî Contrast Minimum): Normal text (below 18pt / 14pt bold): contrast ratio ‚â• 4.5:1. Large text (18pt+ / 14pt+ bold): contrast ratio ‚â• 3:1. Verify `--muted-foreground` against all background tokens ‚Äî borderline at 4.48:1 currently.
- MUST (SC 1.4.4 ‚Äî Resize Text): UI must remain functional when text is resized up to 200%. Use `rem`-based sizing, never fixed `px` for font sizes on the root element. The AccessibilityContext font size control must use CSS classes or rem scale factor, not `root.style.fontSize = 'Xpx'`.
- MUST (SC 1.4.10 ‚Äî Reflow): Content must reflow at 320px CSS width (1280px at 400% zoom) with no horizontal scrolling for vertical content.
- MUST (SC 1.4.11 ‚Äî Non-text Contrast): UI components and graphical objects require ‚â• 3:1 contrast against adjacent colors. This includes form field borders, focus indicators, chart segments, and icon buttons.
- MUST (SC 1.4.12 ‚Äî Text Spacing): No loss of content or functionality when user overrides: line-height to 1.5√ó, paragraph spacing to 2√ó, letter-spacing to 0.12em, word-spacing to 0.16em.
- MUST (SC 1.4.13 ‚Äî Content on Hover or Focus): Tooltips, popovers, and hover content must be dismissible (Escape key), hoverable (mouse can move into the tooltip), and persistent (stays visible until dismissed or trigger loses focus/hover).

---

## 2. Operable

### 2.1 Keyboard Accessible

- MUST (SC 2.1.1 ‚Äî Keyboard): Every interactive element is fully operable via keyboard alone. This includes all buttons, links, tabs, dropdowns, modals, and table actions.
- MUST (SC 2.1.2 ‚Äî No Keyboard Trap): Focus must never become trapped. Modals must trap focus internally but release it on close. Verify Radix Dialog, Popover, and DropdownMenu components handle this correctly.
- SHOULD (SC 2.1.4 ‚Äî Character Key Shortcuts): If single-character keyboard shortcuts are added (e.g., `?` for help), provide a mechanism to remap or disable them.

### 2.2 Enough Time

- MUST (SC 2.2.1 ‚Äî Timing Adjustable): If any session timeouts or auto-refresh are implemented, users must be able to extend or disable them.
- SHOULD (SC 2.2.6 ‚Äî Timeouts): Warn users of data loss from inactivity timeouts. Preserve form data where possible.

### 2.3 Seizures and Physical Reactions

- MUST (SC 2.3.1 ‚Äî Three Flashes): No content flashes more than three times per second.
- MUST (SC 2.3.3 ‚Äî Animation from Interactions): All motion animations MUST respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`. When reduced motion is active, disable transforms, slides, and bounces ‚Äî use opacity-only transitions or instant state changes. The existing `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` block in `index.css` must be maintained and extended to cover all new animations.

### 2.4 Navigable

- MUST (SC 2.4.1 ‚Äî Bypass Blocks): Maintain the existing skip link. It must remain the first focusable element and target `<main>`.
- MUST (SC 2.4.2 ‚Äî Page Titled): Every route must set a unique, descriptive `<title>` via `document.title` or a helmet equivalent. Format: `{PageName} ‚Äî UEM Console`.
- MUST (SC 2.4.3 ‚Äî Focus Order): Focus order follows visual layout order. Tab sequence must be logical and predictable. Never use positive `tabIndex` values (only `0` or `-1`).
- MUST (SC 2.4.5 ‚Äî Multiple Ways): Provide at least two ways to reach any page: sidebar navigation plus at least one of breadcrumbs, search, or command palette (‚åòK).
- MUST (SC 2.4.6 ‚Äî Headings and Labels): Headings are descriptive. Form labels clearly describe purpose. Avoid ambiguous labels like "Submit" without context.
- MUST (SC 2.4.7 ‚Äî Focus Visible): All focusable elements must have a clearly visible focus indicator. Use `--tw-ring-color` and `--tw-ring-offset-color` with Tailwind's `ring` utilities. Never use raw `ring-color:` ‚Äî it is not a valid CSS property.
- MUST (SC 2.4.11 ‚Äî Focus Not Obscured, Minimum): When an element receives focus, it must not be entirely hidden by sticky headers, modals, or other fixed-position elements. The sticky header (`sticky top-0`) must not cover focused content. Implement scroll-margin-top on focusable elements below sticky containers.
- SHOULD (SC 2.4.8 ‚Äî Location): Implement breadcrumb navigation on all pages with nested routes. The existing `breadcrumb.tsx` component must be integrated into `MainLayout` below the header.
- SHOULD: Manage focus on route changes ‚Äî move focus to the page heading or main content area when navigating via the sidebar or breadcrumbs.

### 2.5 Input Modalities

- MUST (SC 2.5.2 ‚Äî Pointer Cancellation): For click/tap actions, use `onClick` (fires on release). Never bind destructive actions to `mousedown` or `touchstart`.
- MUST (SC 2.5.3 ‚Äî Label in Name): The accessible name of a component must contain its visible text label. If a button says "Export", its `aria-label` must include "Export".
- MUST (SC 2.5.7 ‚Äî Dragging Movements): Any drag-and-drop interaction (e.g., dashboard widget reordering) must have a non-drag alternative such as arrow-key reordering or a move-to menu.
- MUST (SC 2.5.8 ‚Äî Target Size, Minimum): All interactive targets must be at least 24√ó24 CSS pixels, or have sufficient spacing (at least 24px between the target's edge and the nearest adjacent target). Inline text links within paragraphs are exempt.

